## Document Quality

**Only real, complete documents are created. No placeholder files.**

- ✅ Documents contain substantive content, not just "Pending" status
- ✅ All required sections are filled in
- ✅ Proper citations included (if AI-generated)
- ❌ No placeholder templates or empty files
- ❌ No files that only contain "To be generated" messages

**See Rule 004 (Core Document Quality) for complete requirements.**

## Summary

1. **Discovery docs**: `/docs/discovery/` with `NARRATIVE-`, `NICHE-INTEL-`, `PAIN-SIGNALS-`, `JTBD-`, `OPPORTUNITY-`, `REDTEAM-` prefixes
2. **Validation docs**: `/docs/validation/` with `VALIDATION-PLAN-`, `LANDING-`, `DISTRIBUTION-`, `PRICING-TEST-`, `CREATIVE-BATCH-`, `RESULTS-`, `REDTEAM-` prefixes
3. **Automation specs**: `/docs/automation/lindy/` with `LINDY-SPEC-` prefix
4. **Idea slug**: Lowercase, hyphenated, descriptive, consistent across all docs
5. **One idea = one full doc set**: All docs for an idea share the same `<idea-slug>`
6. **Real files only**: No placeholder files, use README for status tracking

**This prevents chaos by ensuring every idea has a complete, organized document set in predictable locations.**

